		<div class="right"><a href="index.html"><img src="../sle.png" alt="SLE 2023"></a><br><code>sle2023/paper03</code></div>
			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2023</a> paper:</span><br><i>Adaptive Structural Operational Semantics</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/GwendalJouneaux.html">Gwendal Jouneaux</a>, <a href="../profile/DamianFrölich.html">Damian Frölich</a>, <a href="../profile/OlivierBarais.html">Olivier Barais</a>, <a href="../profile/BenoîtCombemale.html">Benoît Combemale</a>, <a href="../profile/GurvanLeGuernic.html">Gurvan Le Guernic</a>, <a href="../profile/GunterMussbacher.html">Gunter Mussbacher</a>, <a href="../profile/LThomasvanBinsbergen.html">L. Thomas van Binsbergen</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/3623476.3623517">10.1145/3623476.3623517</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1c.html"><span class="tagM">T1C: Behavioural Semantics</span></a><ul><li> The paper introduces a variant of structural operational semantics aimed at specifying adaptive program behavior.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4d.html"><span class="tagL">T4D: Interpretation</span></a><ul><li> The semantics explicitly targets runtime adaptation mechanisms that influence execution during operation.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3c.html"><span class="tagL">T3C: DSLs</span></a><ul><li> The motivation is to make self-adaptation easier to add in domain-specific settings where adaptation is a secondary concern.
</li></ul></li></ul>
